Got a response from sfk's developer of how to append/insert text lines by means of sfk:To append several lines similar tocmd /c echo trailing line1>>myfile.txtcmd /c echo trailing line2>>myfile.txtuse the following:sfk echo -spat "trailing line1\ntrailing line2" +append myfile.txtExample to insert some text before line 5:sfk filt -lnum in.txt +xed "/[lstart]005 /005 text to insert\n[all]/" +xed "/[lstart]* //"Example to insert after a specific string (e.g. insert after a line that contains a string "insert something after me"):sfk xed in.txt "/[lstart]*insert something after me*[eol]/[all]the new text\n/"set compact=ctext_saveto D:\tmp.jsoncmd /C "jq -r$(compact) . D:\tmp.json > D:\dst.json"if $(EXITCODE)==0  text_loadfrom D:\dst.jsonendifNppExec v0.6 RC2 (a version being developed currently) will allow to replacesci_sendmsg SCI_GETCODEPAGEset local sci_cp = $(MSG_RESULT)if $(sci_cp) == 65001 // UTF-8  set local str_len ~ strlenutf8 $(str)else  set local str_len ~ strlen $(str)endifwith justset local str_len ~ strlensci $(str)